simulator.grocery

Interface GroceryInterface


  • public interface GroceryInterface
    A GroceryInterface describes an item that is available. for sale in a GroceryStore
    Author:
    jcollard, jddevaug

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      double getCost()
      Returns the cost of this GroceryInterface.
      double getHandlingRating()
      Returns a number between [0, 1] that describes the difficulty to handle this GroceryInterface where 0 is not difficult at all and 1 is extremely difficult.
      java.lang.String getName()
      Returns the name of this GroceryInterface.
      double getPrice()
      Returns the price of this GroceryInterface.

      • getName

        java.lang.String getName()
        Returns the name of this GroceryInterface.

      • getPrice

        double getPrice()
        Returns the price of this GroceryInterface. This is the amount that a Shopper must pay to purchase the item. This must be a value greater than or equal to 0.
        Returns:
        the price of this GroceryInterface

      • getCost

        double getCost()
        Returns the cost of this GroceryInterface. This is the amount that a GroceryStore pays a vendor for the item. This must be a value greater than 0.
        Returns:
        the cost of this GroceryInterface

      • getHandlingRating

        double getHandlingRating()
        Returns a number between [0, 1] that describes the difficulty to handle this GroceryInterface where 0 is not difficult at all and 1 is extremely difficult.
        Returns:
        the handling rating associated with this GroceryInterface
